Friday, 31st July 2020, as been declared as the day of Eid-el-Kabir by the Sultan of Sokoto, Alhaji Muhammad Abubakar.<img src="https://i1.wp.com/instablog9ja.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instablog9ja_20200723_30.jpg?resize=1024%2C1024" />He also advised on how to observe prayers across the country amid the Covid-19 pandemic. According to him: “In view of the current situation caused by the Covid-19 pandemic, the Sultan hereby advises all the District Heads and Imams in Sokoto State to observe Eid prayers in their Jumu’at mosques in their respective towns and villages and not at Eid grounds. Also, the council advises the muslim communities throughout the country to observe Eid prayers at Jumu’at Mosques to help curb the spread of Covid-19.” Original Article Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world.